This paper discusses transfer learning in the context of adversarial robustness, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of feature extractors and fine-tuning, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with the issue of adversarial attacks, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR).
